td.paragraph: Labs
were reviewed and discussed today revealing an A1C of 6.2, consistent
with prediabetes. CMP, CBC, lipid panel, hepatic function, thyroid
function, vitamin D, and apolipoprotein studies were all reviewed and
noted to be within or near normal limits. We counseled the patient on
the importance of a low-glycemic, heart-healthy diet, regular
exercise, and weight reduction to address prediabetes and prevent
progression to type 2 diabetes mellitus. She is scheduled to follow
up in the office on 07/29 for continued cardiovascular evaluation and
monitoring of metabolic parameters. She agrees with the proposed plan
of care.

Patient was informed of the telemedicine visit by our office staff. Telemedicine was described in detail to the patient as the use of synchronous video and audio communication to provide clinical care from a distance. A telemedicine visit can provide the same medical standard of care for specific conditions. The patient was informed that the practice staff located at the provider's office would assist in carrying out any recommendations and clinical care.
Patient Location: Home
Lack of strict HIPPA Rules. Patient expressed verbal interest in the telemedicine visit and granted consent to proceed.
